WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:02.130
MALE SPEAKER: So good
afternoon, everyone.

00:00:02.130 --> 00:00:05.690
Welcome to another outstanding
Authors at Google talk.

00:00:05.690 --> 00:00:08.730
Today we're pleased to host
a Mike Marriner and the

00:00:08.730 --> 00:00:13.110
co-founders of the Roadtrip
Nation organization.

00:00:13.110 --> 00:00:15.570
What is Roadtrip Nation,
you may ask?

00:00:15.570 --> 00:00:17.800
It's outstanding example
of a dream that,

00:00:17.800 --> 00:00:19.230
actually, never dies.

00:00:19.230 --> 00:00:20.090
It keeps on going.

00:00:20.090 --> 00:00:22.830
So back in college, Mike
and his friends went

00:00:22.830 --> 00:00:23.770
on this road trip.

00:00:23.770 --> 00:00:25.050
They interviewed a few people.

00:00:25.050 --> 00:00:27.030
They posted some
videos online.

00:00:27.030 --> 00:00:29.420
It became this long
going tradition.

00:00:29.420 --> 00:00:31.910
And one road trip leads to
another, leads to another and,

00:00:31.910 --> 00:00:33.750
in this case, leads
to a company.

00:00:33.750 --> 00:00:37.470
So not only do they have a PBS
series that was picked up,

00:00:37.470 --> 00:00:40.320
detailing their adventures,
but they have a foundation

00:00:40.320 --> 00:00:43.800
that encourages high school
and college kids to start

00:00:43.800 --> 00:00:46.280
their own road trip to really
explore their own communities.

00:00:46.280 --> 00:00:49.190
And so they'll tell us what
they're up to, most recently.

00:00:49.190 --> 00:00:50.690
And we'll also play a video.

00:00:50.690 --> 00:00:53.247
So Mike, did you want to talk
about video, briefly.

00:00:53.247 --> 00:00:54.740
MIKE MARRINER: Sure.

00:00:54.740 --> 00:00:58.140
I guess we'll begin the story
with the end in mind and show

00:00:58.140 --> 00:01:00.650
a little bit of a video, of a
snapshot of what Roadtrip

00:01:00.650 --> 00:01:04.099
Nation is today, from one of
our recent series on public

00:01:04.099 --> 00:01:04.560
television.

00:01:04.560 --> 00:01:06.910
So we'll just kick it
off with this video.

