-Exactly.

00:44:48.200 --> 00:44:49.440
My whole life would be
completely different.

00:44:49.440 --> 00:44:51.240
-That's incredible.

00:44:51.240 --> 00:44:54.750
-I may have gotten a day job
that would've distracted me,

00:44:54.750 --> 00:44:56.230
whatever it may be.

00:44:56.230 --> 00:44:59.240
I firmly also believe though
that, if you have the desire

00:44:59.240 --> 00:45:01.340
and the passion, which
I did, I would have

00:45:01.340 --> 00:45:02.410
eventually broken in.

00:45:02.410 --> 00:45:04.980
Some people are just incredibly,
naturally talented

00:45:04.980 --> 00:45:07.160
and are born athletes or are
born singers or are born

00:45:07.160 --> 00:45:10.665
artists and they can just, one
day, sit down and just do it.

00:45:10.665 --> 00:45:14.080
But those are the one
in a kazillion that

00:45:14.080 --> 00:45:15.530
can actually do that.

00:45:15.530 --> 00:45:17.850
Everyone else on planet Earth
has to work really, really

00:45:17.850 --> 00:45:18.610
hard for it.

00:45:18.610 --> 00:45:21.120
-You know, as far as like
working, work ethic, you have

00:45:21.120 --> 00:45:21.735
to work hard.

00:45:21.735 --> 00:45:23.600
You know what I mean, like
always work hard?

00:45:23.600 --> 00:45:25.340
Don't expect anybody to
give you anything.

00:45:25.340 --> 00:45:27.825
-It's not like I walked into MTV
and I was like, whoo, I'm

00:45:27.825 --> 00:45:29.010
directing two weeks later.

00:45:29.010 --> 00:45:33.550
I mean, I worked my butt
off for a long time.

00:45:33.550 --> 00:45:38.050
-If you think of your situation
as being like a

00:45:38.050 --> 00:45:41.140
tripod, on three legs
that hit the ground.

00:45:41.140 --> 00:45:43.970
And each of those
legs has a name.

00:45:43.970 --> 00:45:46.250
And one of them is luck.

00:45:46.250 --> 00:45:47.810
The other one is talent.

00:45:47.810 --> 00:45:50.970
And the other one
is hard work.

00:45:50.970 --> 00:45:53.910
Although one of those things
will get you into a situation,

00:45:53.910 --> 00:45:57.640
as quickly as possible, you
have to get another one of

00:45:57.640 --> 00:45:59.680
those tripod legs
on the ground.

00:45:59.680 --> 00:46:02.230
-You just have to run at
something until something is

00:46:02.230 --> 00:46:04.510
talking to your heart loudly
enough that you won't even

00:46:04.510 --> 00:46:08.200
have to wonder if it's
the right thing.

00:46:08.200 --> 00:46:09.770
But you have to run
pretty hard.

00:46:09.770 --> 00:46:11.760
And you have to be a moron
along the way.

00:46:11.760 --> 00:46:13.450
And you have to accept that
there's going to be a lot of

00:46:13.450 --> 00:46:17.140
wasted time and energy and that
that is not a bad thing.

00:46:17.140 --> 00:46:22.570
-It is more important to me to
fulfill this larger goal,

00:46:22.570 --> 00:46:25.890
which I wanted Chicago to have
a Shakespeare theater.

00:46:25.890 --> 00:46:30.200
And so I always came back to
that, in saying, you know

00:46:30.200 --> 00:46:32.330
what, so you're crying.

00:46:32.330 --> 00:46:35.230
So you had a horrible day.

00:46:35.230 --> 00:46:39.460
But you're still doing something
that, if you left,

00:46:39.460 --> 00:46:42.800
you might never forgive
yourself.

00:46:42.800 --> 00:46:44.390
-There was something in me that
just said, you're not

00:46:44.390 --> 00:46:45.310
going to fail.

00:46:45.310 --> 00:46:47.870
It's just how long is it
going to be hard for?

00:46:47.870 --> 00:46:50.290
-Like anything else in
life, it's a huge

00:46:50.290 --> 00:46:50.740
roller coaster ride.

00:46:50.740 --> 00:46:54.230
There can be high times, low
times, happy times, sad times.

00:46:54.230 --> 00:46:59.830
-Will.i.am wore my shoe to,
I think, the BET Awards.

00:46:59.830 --> 00:47:02.860
The shoe got on display
at the DNC.

00:47:02.860 --> 00:47:04.620
And then like the first big
thing to happen was the

00:47:04.620 --> 00:47:05.600
Smithsonian emailing me.

00:47:05.600 --> 00:47:07.562
And I thought it was a joke.

00:47:07.562 --> 00:47:08.110
I was saying, no.

00:47:08.110 --> 00:47:11.030
I had to call the lady and
say, are you serious?

00:47:11.030 --> 00:47:16.030
You want my shoe in the large
museum in the world, a painted

00:47:16.030 --> 00:47:17.400
tennis shoe that I did?

00:47:17.400 --> 00:47:18.950
And she was like,
yes, we want it.

00:47:18.950 --> 00:47:19.630
It's beautiful.

00:47:19.630 --> 00:47:20.420
And I cried.

00:47:20.420 --> 00:47:24.520
I was like, I was almost
homeless in January.

00:47:24.520 --> 00:47:28.992
Had I quit a month before I made
that shoe, if I quit an

00:47:28.992 --> 00:47:31.510
hour before I made that shoe
and decided, I'm just going

00:47:31.510 --> 00:47:34.560
forget my art, this would've
never happened.

00:47:34.560 --> 00:47:35.290
I could've quit.

00:47:35.290 --> 00:47:37.705
I was about to be kicked
out of my house.

00:47:37.705 --> 00:47:40.150
And I didn't quit and then
look what happened.

00:47:40.150 --> 00:47:43.020
-One thing that does give me
satisfaction, when I sit back

00:47:43.020 --> 00:47:46.010
and think about what could have
happened, what if I'd

00:47:46.010 --> 00:47:50.680
just got a job doing something
that I didn't enjoy and stayed

00:47:50.680 --> 00:47:55.120
back in Boston and was with the
guys I grew up with and

00:47:55.120 --> 00:47:58.740
didn't really evolve and grow
and change and be the person I

00:47:58.740 --> 00:47:59.270
could've been?

00:47:59.270 --> 00:48:01.930
That give me satisfaction, when
I look back and go, wow,

00:48:01.930 --> 00:48:02.960
I don't even really work.

00:48:02.960 --> 00:48:04.860
I'm doing what I love to do.

00:48:04.860 --> 00:48:05.400
It's fun.

00:48:05.400 --> 00:48:09.260
-The UG named me reporter
of the year, last year.

00:48:09.260 --> 00:48:10.000
And I can't believe it.

00:48:10.000 --> 00:48:13.130
I can't believe that I'm getting
to do exactly what I

00:48:13.130 --> 00:48:14.050
wanted to do.

00:48:14.050 --> 00:48:16.340
I'm seriously, seriously
living my dreams.

00:48:16.340 --> 00:48:17.200
See, I'm getting emotional.

00:48:17.200 --> 00:48:20.140
Because I really didn't think
this was going to happen.

00:48:20.140 --> 00:48:21.190
And it's happening.

00:48:21.190 --> 00:48:24.270
So to you guys, I say,
just keep fighting,

00:48:24.270 --> 00:48:25.734
keep doing your thing.

