00:50:03.440 --> 00:50:04.950
MIKE MARRINER: Just to end on
impact, what we've been

00:50:04.950 --> 00:50:06.860
learning, lately, in education,
is that you can't

00:50:06.860 --> 00:50:08.650
just go into the education world
and say, we're going to

00:50:08.650 --> 00:50:09.820
inspire people.

00:50:09.820 --> 00:50:11.810
There's a responsibility, when
you're working with students,

00:50:11.810 --> 00:50:13.890
especially students in the
communities where we work.

00:50:13.890 --> 00:50:16.905
And so over the last year, the
Hewlett Foundation has funded

00:50:16.905 --> 00:50:19.615
a third party efficacy study on
Roadtrip Nation's expansion

00:50:19.615 --> 00:50:21.990
and proliferation through
these school systems and

00:50:21.990 --> 00:50:23.670
trying to really ascertain,
what is the impact we're

00:50:23.670 --> 00:50:25.390
really having on
these students?

00:50:25.390 --> 00:50:26.510
And essentially, what
they've been

00:50:26.510 --> 00:50:29.130
finding is that students--

00:50:29.130 --> 00:50:31.170
through different modalities,
in terms of how they've

00:50:31.170 --> 00:50:32.420
researched this--

00:50:35.270 --> 00:50:37.530
self-efficacy rates, which is,
essentially, students'

00:50:37.530 --> 00:50:40.790
self-belief in their ability to
solve complex problems and

00:50:40.790 --> 00:50:43.780
more the non-cognitive senses,
in terms of their belief in

00:50:43.780 --> 00:50:45.980
themselves and their futures,
have increased

00:50:45.980 --> 00:50:47.920
at significant rates.

00:50:47.920 --> 00:50:51.440
But also, their GPA rates
have been increasing.

00:50:51.440 --> 00:50:54.470
So this study just came out
last week, by a Dr. David

00:50:54.470 --> 00:50:55.000
[? Connelly ?].

00:50:55.000 --> 00:50:57.480
But it found that students, in
a comparison study, in San

00:50:57.480 --> 00:50:59.960
Jose Unified School District,
in credit recovery settings,

00:50:59.960 --> 00:51:03.230
the most at-risk students,
when the Roadtrip Nation

00:51:03.230 --> 00:51:06.330
students, over a nine month
period, had twice the rate of

00:51:06.330 --> 00:51:09.320
GPA increase, when compared to
the non-Roadtrip students, in

00:51:09.320 --> 00:51:12.240
the exact same socioeconomic
and demographic settings.

00:51:12.240 --> 00:51:14.120
And the researcher said this
was interesting, because

00:51:14.120 --> 00:51:17.140
Roadtrip Nation, nowhere in
our curriculum do we say,

00:51:17.140 --> 00:51:19.720
study hard, get good grades,
follow the standards, all

00:51:19.720 --> 00:51:20.190
those things.

00:51:20.190 --> 00:51:23.000
It's all kind of connected to
the new common core standards

00:51:23.000 --> 00:51:25.220
for ELA anchor standards on the
back end, so it's legit

00:51:25.220 --> 00:51:26.520
from a district standpoint.

00:51:26.520 --> 00:51:29.630
But we focus more on the
self-efficacy component.

00:51:29.630 --> 00:51:32.110
Students taking ownership over
their futures and actually

00:51:32.110 --> 00:51:34.100
being an active participant in
what they want to do with

00:51:34.100 --> 00:51:34.800
their life.

00:51:34.800 --> 00:51:37.450
And by focusing on those more
upstream, self-efficacy

00:51:37.450 --> 00:51:40.780
factors, we start to see
downstream academic gain start

00:51:40.780 --> 00:51:42.030
to increase.

00:51:43.660 --> 00:51:45.365
It's an interesting part of
the journey for Roadtrip

00:51:45.365 --> 00:51:47.250
Nation, because.

00:51:47.250 --> 00:51:48.910
It is our 10th year anniversary

00:51:48.910 --> 00:51:49.616
for Roadtrip Nation.

00:51:49.616 --> 00:51:52.720
But we really feel like it's
beginning of an entire new 10

00:51:52.720 --> 00:51:54.980
year chapter, where
were continuing to

00:51:54.980 --> 00:51:56.250
proliferate the movement.

00:51:56.250 --> 00:51:59.100
And we're just scratching the
surface on what we can do.

00:51:59.100 --> 00:52:02.210
So we just want to thank you
guys for staying here for

00:52:02.210 --> 00:52:03.700
lunch and listening
to our story.

